{"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/Moon","doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/MoonPhase","doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/MoonQuarter","doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/Libration","doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/LunarNode","doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/NodeKind"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Moon","title":"Moon"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/MoonPhases"},"kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Calculate moon phases, quarters, libration, and lunar nodes.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/astronomykit\/moonphases"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit"]]},"sections":[],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Moon Phases","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"AstronomyKit"}]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/Moon","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" type provides comprehensive lunar calculations including phase angles, illumination, quarter searches, libration data, and node crossings."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Phase Angle","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Phase-Angle"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The phase angle indicates the Moon’s position in its cycle:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let angle = try Moon.phaseAngle(at: .now)","print(\"Phase angle: \\(angle)°\")","\/\/ 0° = New Moon, 90° = First Quarter, 180° = Full, 270° = Third Quarter"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Phase Names and Emoji","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Phase-Names-and-Emoji"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Convert angles to human-readable descriptions:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let angle = try Moon.phaseAngle(at: .now)","","print(Moon.phaseName(for: angle))  \/\/ \"Waxing Gibbous\"","print(Moon.emoji(for: angle))      \/\/ \"🌔\""],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The eight phase names:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"New Moon (🌑)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Waxing Crescent (🌒)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"First Quarter (🌓)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Waxing Gibbous (🌔)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Full Moon (🌕)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Waning Gibbous (🌖)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Third Quarter (🌗)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Waning Crescent (🌘)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"text":"Illumination","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Illumination"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Calculate the fraction of the Moon that’s lit:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let angle = try Moon.phaseAngle(at: .now)","let illumination = Moon.illumination(for: angle)","print(\"Moon is \\(Int(illumination * 100))% illuminated\")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Finding Quarter Phases","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Finding-Quarter-Phases"},{"text":"Search for a Specific Phase","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Search-for-a-Specific-Phase"},{"code":["\/\/ Next full moon (nil if none occurs within the search window)","if let fullMoon = try Moon.searchPhase(.full, after: .now) {","    print(\"Next full moon: \\(fullMoon)\")","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Get the Next Quarter","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Get-the-Next-Quarter"},{"code":["let quarter = try Moon.searchQuarter(after: .now)","print(\"\\(quarter.phase.emoji) \\(quarter.phase.name) at \\(quarter.time)\")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"text":"All Quarters in a Date Range","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"All-Quarters-in-a-Date-Range"},{"code":["let start = AstroTime(year: 2025, month: 1, day: 1)","let end = AstroTime(year: 2025, month: 2, day: 1)","","let quarters = try Moon.quarters(from: start, to: end)","for quarter in quarters {","    print(\"\\(quarter.phase.emoji) \\(quarter.time)\")","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Lunar Position","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Lunar-Position"},{"text":"Ecliptic Coordinates","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Ecliptic-Coordinates"},{"code":["let position = try Moon.ecliptic(at: .now)","print(\"Longitude: \\(position.longitude)°\")","print(\"Latitude: \\(position.latitude)°\")","print(\"Distance: \\(position.distance) AU\")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Moon State (Position and Velocity)","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Moon-State-Position-and-Velocity"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get the Moon’s complete state vector including velocity:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let state = try Moon.geoState(at: .now)","","\/\/ Position in AU","print(\"Distance: \\(state.position.magnitude) AU\")","","\/\/ Velocity in AU\/day","let speed = sqrt(","    state.velocity.x * state.velocity.x +","    state.velocity.y * state.velocity.y +","    state.velocity.z * state.velocity.z",")","print(\"Speed: \\(speed) AU\/day\")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"name":"Tip","style":"tip","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"geoState(at:)"},{"text":" for velocity calculations instead of differencing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"ecliptic longitude positions, which gives inaccurate results.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"text":"Using CelestialBody","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Using-CelestialBody"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Moon is also available as a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/CelestialBody","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let horizon = try CelestialBody.moon.horizon(at: .now, from: observer)","let equatorial = try CelestialBody.moon.equatorial(at: .now)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Libration","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Libration"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Libration is the Moon’s apparent wobble that lets us see slightly more than 50% of its surface:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let lib = Moon.libration(at: .now)","","\/\/ Sub-Earth point (what's at the center of the visible disc)","print(\"Latitude: \\(lib.subEarthLatitude)°\")","print(\"Longitude: \\(lib.subEarthLongitude)°\")","","\/\/ Distance and apparent size","print(\"Distance: \\(Int(lib.distanceKM)) km\")","print(\"Apparent diameter: \\(lib.apparentDiameter)°\")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Interpret libration values:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Positive latitude: More of the north polar region is visible"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Positive longitude: More of the Moon’s east limb is visible"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"text":"Lunar Nodes","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Lunar-Nodes"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The nodes are where the Moon’s orbit crosses the ecliptic plane:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\/\/ Find next node crossing","let node = try Moon.searchNode(after: .now)","print(\"\\(node.kind.symbol) \\(node.kind.name) at \\(node.time)\")","\/\/ Output: \"☊ Ascending Node at 2025-01-15...\""],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Node Types","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Node-Types"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Ascending (☊)","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Moon crosses from south to north of the ecliptic"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Descending (☋)","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Moon crosses from north to south"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"text":"All Nodes in a Range","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"All-Nodes-in-a-Range"},{"code":["let nodes = try Moon.nodeCrossings(","    from: AstroTime(year: 2025, month: 1, day: 1),","    to: AstroTime(year: 2025, month: 12, day: 31)",")","for node in nodes {","    print(\"\\(node.kind.symbol) \\(node.time)\")","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Lunar Apsis","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Lunar-Apsis"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Find perigee (closest) and apogee (farthest) points:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let apsis = try Moon.searchApsis(after: .now)","print(\"\\(apsis.kind.lunarName): \\(Int(apsis.distanceKM)) km\")","\/\/ Output: \"Perigee: 356,500 km\""],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"text":"All Apsides in a Range","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"All-Apsides-in-a-Range"},{"code":["let apsides = try Moon.apsides(","    from: .now,","    to: .now.addingDays(60)",")","for apsis in apsides {","    print(\"\\(apsis.kind.lunarName) at \\(apsis.time)\")","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Moonrise and Moonset","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Moonrise-and-Moonset"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/CelestialBody","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" interface:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"cod